This paper deals with the analysis of language using network methods, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of community detection algorithms to identify relevant topics, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also proposes a novel network representation to capture semantic relationships, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the organization of topics, which could be related to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
